modules.description: This module implements an HTTP/2 client that initiates and manages HTTP/2 connections over a provided flow. It supports sending requests with optional trailers, handling server responses and push promises, and issuing ping frames. Concrete use cases include making HTTP/2 requests over TLS or TCP flows, handling server push, and managing connection lifecycle events.

This module implements HTTP/2 client and server functionality for MirageOS-compatible flows and sockets. The server module handles incoming HTTP/2 requests and errors over a socket, while the client module sends requests, handles responses, and manages connection events over a flow. Use cases include building HTTP/2 servers that process client requests on MirageOS targets and implementing HTTP/2 clients that perform secure requests with TLS or handle server push.
